The issue with the code is that the `getSupportActionBar()` method returns `null` if the `ActionBar` is not present in the current theme. To fix this issue, you can use the `setDisplayShowHomeEnabled()` method of the `ActionBar` to enable the home indicator, even if the `ActionBar` is not present.

Here's the updated code:
```java
public class DishTag extends ActionBarActivity implements OnClickListener {
    // ...
    @Override
    protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
        setContentView(R.layout.dish_tag);
        context = this;
        // ...
        ActionBar actionBar = getSupportActionBar();
        if (actionBar != null) {
            actionBar.setDisplayShowHomeEnabled(true);
            actionBar.setTitle("SD");
        }
    }
}
```
By using the `getSupportActionBar()` method to check if the `ActionBar` is not null, and then using the `setDisplayShowHomeEnabled()` method to enable the home indicator, you can avoid the `NullPointerException` and ensure that the `ActionBar` is properly initialized.
